autoreadme — fork notice
=========================

This is a fork of github.com/jimmyfrasche/autoreadme.

Fork point: commit aacd7e11c8ba0b1f62709fd5d195d2cc48d90af4 (2024-05-04).
Upstream license (BSD-2-Clause, "Copyright (c) 2013, JImmyFrasche") is
retained verbatim in LICENSE and continues to apply to the inherited code.

Why the fork: upstream is unmaintained and we hit a real bug (below) with no
prospect of an upstream fix. The tool is small and build-time only, so we own
it rather than depend on a dead repo.

Module path / hosting
---------------------
Published under the vanity import path omz13.com/go/autoreadme. Source is
hosted at github.com/omz13/autoreadme; the vanity path carries the go-import
redirect. The original github.com/jimmyfrasche/autoreadme import path is no
longer used by our tree.

Changes from the fork point
---------------------------
- project.go, PairPackagesWithXTests: the merged *info was stored under
  pkg.PkgPath but looked up under the _test-stripped path. With go/packages
  returning an external test package (package foo_test) before its in-package
  sibling, the lookup missed and produced a phantom info with pkg == nil.
  CollectProjectErrors then flagged that as "only has external test files"
  and aborted the WHOLE run, writing zero READMEs — silently and
  nondeterministically, depending on load order. Now keyed under the stripped
  path so the pair merges regardless of order.
- go.mod: module renamed to omz13.com/go/autoreadme; golang.org/x/tools,
  x/mod and x/sync bumped so the tool builds under the current Go toolchain
  (the pinned x/tools no longer compiled).
- default.template: generated footers now link to
  https://pkg.go.dev/omz13.com/go/autoreadme, the human-readable docs page for
  the vanity import path.
- files.go: readFile now returns unexpected os.ReadFile errors instead of
  silently treating them as empty content. Missing files are still optional.
- autoreadme.go: added -check for CI drift detection (dry run, non-zero when
  any README.md is stale) and -v for stable reporting of skipped, unchanged and
  written files. Changed output paths are sorted so logs are deterministic.
- tests: added focused coverage for the external-test-package pairing bug and
  readFile error propagation.
